Rfmalloc bundles or adapts the following third-party code. The package
itself is licensed GPL (>= 2); the components below remain under their
upstream licenses, which are GPL-compatible, and their required notices are
preserved here.

Component: fmalloc allocator runtime (inst/fmalloc/)
Upstream: https://github.com/yasukata/fmalloc (patched copy)
See inst/fmalloc for its license and provenance notes.

Component: ALP scalar encode/decode core (src/fmalloc_alp.inc)
Adapted from: Mike Cheng's C implementation in the zap package,
  https://github.com/coolbutuseless/zap (src/utils-alp.c), MIT License,
  Copyright (c) Mike Cheng (mikefc@coolbutuseless.com).
Algorithm: Afroozeh, Kuffo, Boncz — "ALP: Adaptive Lossless floating-Point
  Compression" (doi:10.1145/3626717). Reference C++ implementation:
  https://github.com/cwida/ALP (MIT).
The adaptation covers the decimal-scaling round-trip test, exponent tables,
fast rounding, and the encode/decode loops; the chunked payload container,
per-chunk probing, bit packing, and patch layout are Rfmalloc's own.

